      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "**It's a standard, but very good-paying, doctor's office. DR. BUZZWIG (40s, impossibly slicked-back hair, wearing a lab coat that looks borrowed from a Bond villain) leans back in his chair, one leg crossed over the other. Across from him sits PATIENT MARTHA (30s), looking visibly uncomfortable and slightly worried.**\n\n<center>DR. BUZZWIG</center>\n> (A booming, self-satisfied drawl, waving a dismissive hand mid-air)\n> Listen up, dollface. Pseudoephedrine. Big pharma drama, big fuss.\n\n<center>PATIENT MARTHA</center>\n> (Frowning, clutching her chest lightly)\n> But Doctor, I've been feeling this... this pounding in my head, and I'm pregnant.\n\nDr. Buzzwig lets out a short, theatrical chuckle, a sound that suggests he finds her concern mildly amusing.\n\n<center>DR. BUZZWIG</center>\n> Pounding? Nah. That's just your hormones putting on a little show. A little *drama*. Look, these little chemicals—they",
