    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "**INT. DOCTOR'S OFFICE - DAY**\n\nThe office is offensively bright, adorned with motivational posters featuring suspiciously cheerful stock photos of healthy babies. DR. BUZZWIG (40s, impeccably tailored, swagger dripping from every movement) leans over his desk toward PATIENT MARTHA (30s, looking utterly drained).\n\nDr. Buzzwig throws his hands up mid-sentence, a dazzling, utterly unconcerned grin plastered on his face. His practiced charisma is dialed up to eleven.\n\n<center>DR. BUZZWIG</center>\n> (Waving a dismissive hand, a flourish more than a gesture)\n> Hormones, dollface, they’re a whole thing. Big deal. But listen up, and this is where you shine.\n\nHe leans in conspiratorially, but his tone is pure bravado.\n\n<center>DR. BUZZWIG</center>\n> This fuss about those stimulants? The blood pressure jitters, the little palpitations you're having? Nah. Skip the fuss. Seriously. Let the system breathe.\n\nHe straightens up, puffing out his chest slightly, as if delivering a profound piece of common sense,",
